THOUGHT: The crash arises because VPTransformState::get is asked for a vector value for a VPReplicateRecipe that only set a scalar (uniform case). In VPReplicateRecipe::execute, when IsUniform, we only scalarize lane 0 and return without setting a vector, so later a vector get() asserts. The fix is to, after scalarizing lane 0 under IsUniform and VF is vector, create a splat vector from the scalar and register it via State.set(this, Vec). I will modify LoopVectorize.cpp to insert this splat before the return in the IsUniform branch.

```bash
sed -i '/if (IsUniform) {/,+5s/State\.ILV->scalarizeInstruction(UI, this, VPLane(0), State);/State.ILV->scalarizeInstruction(UI, this, VPLane(0), State);
    if (State.VF.isVector()) {
      Value *Scalar = State.get(this, VPLane(0));
      Value *Vec = State.Builder.CreateVectorSplat(State.VF, Scalar, "uniform.splat");
      State.set(this, Vec);
    }/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp && submit-patch
```

